-dimensional and compelling analyses. Bringing together both theoretical and practical material, this book shows researchers how ethnography can be carried out within human service settings. It provides an invaluable guide on how to apply ethnographic creativeness and offers a more humanistic and context-sensitive approach in the field of health and social care to generating valid knowledge about today's service work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Human Services.2bisacsh1 aAredes, Janaína, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAvendal, Christel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBartoszko, Aleksandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBengtsson, Tea Torbenfeldt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngel, Cíntia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGubrium, Jaber F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGubrium, Jaber, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJacobsson, Katarina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobsson, Katarina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJefferson, Andrew M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeibing, Annette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLydahl, Doris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMik-Meyer, Nanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPösö, Tarja, econtributor.4ctb4https://